		<td width="617"><div id="homecontent"><h1>Hotel Palomar - A San Francisco Union Square Hotel that is Art in Motion</h1>
		
		<p>An artful urban retreat in the heart of downtown San Francisco is Hotel Palomar. Hidden five floors above the city hustle and bustle and just steps away from ever-busy San Francisco Union Square, the hotel, a Kimpton Hotel, is like a great painting waiting to be discovered  by the discerning traveler.<br /><br />
		
		The style of this San Francisco luxury hotel is contemporary but not trendy, with playful touches throughout. The d&eacute;cor invites closer inspection that reveals artful details, such as the lobby's stunning parquet floors reminiscent of the geometric drawings of M.C. Escher. The atmosphere recalls Paris of the 1930s, where artists and intellectuals chatted at sidewalk cafes in an imaginative city full of creative energy, just like modern day San Francisco.<br /><br />
		
		Located at 4th Street and Market, Hotel Palomar is centrally located near three of the city's most dynamic districts: the thriving South of Market (SOMA) district, the Financial District, and San Francisco Union Square, famous for its great shopping. This sophisticated boutique hotel is just a short walk from Moscone Convention Center and great art museums, such as SF MOMA.<br /><br />
		
		With a reputation for high-touch service and individual attention, Hotel Palomar is a study in the Art of Service and reflects the standards expected from a Kimpton Hotel. The luxury <strong>Hotel Palomar was awarded Conde Naste Traveler's 2005 Gold List of the World's Best Places to Stay</strong>, and this dynamic California hotel also received the prestigious AAA Four Diamond hotel award, a trend unbroken since the hotel opened in 1999.<br /><br />
		
			<img src="images/bullet.gif" width="5" height="5" alt="" class="hphoriz">Complimentary wireless Internet access<br />
